cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a non-standard computational model of linear logic using lambda calculus. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a PCF-like lambda calculus with booleans. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses two finite models, one based on finite sets and the other on finite vector spaces. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility as the paper discusses an algebraic extension of the finite lambda calculus. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses completeness of the finite models with respect to the operational semantics of the language.
